claim: Vaccination with a higher-dose recombinant flu vaccine may induce a more robust antibody response than egg-based standard-dose vaccines.
explanation: A table listing influenza vaccine products by trade name (manufacturer), presentation, age indication, antigen content per dose (µg HA for inactivated vaccines or virus count for live attenuated), administration route, and mercury content. It includes Fluad Quadrivalent (egg-based standard-dose, 15 µg HA per strain, ≥65 yrs), Flublok Quadrivalent (recombinant HA, 45 µg HA per strain, ≥18 yrs), and FluMist Quadrivalent (egg-based live attenuated intranasal). The table only reports vaccine formulations and antigen doses; it does not present any immunogenicity or antibody response data, so it does not support the claim. Note: No antibody titer or comparative immunogenicity data are shown; conclusions about immune responses cannot be drawn from this dosage table alone.
